translated: Holmberg, Carl Henrik was a music director and city librarian in Tidaholm. He was born January 19th, 1877 in Södertälje to parents Carl G.H. and Anna Juliana Becker. He married Gulli Zander in 1903 and they had five children: Henrik Georg born in 1905, Carl Gustaf born in 1907, Stig Olof born in 1910, Ingrid Elisabet born in 1917, and Anna Margareta born in 1919. He graduated as a music director from the Music High School in 1913 and completed library courses at the School Superintendent's Office in 1931. He was a music volunteer at Svea Livgardet from 1891-1897, a music non-commissioned officer at Smålands artilleriregemente from 1898-1914, a music director at Skaraborgs regemente from 1914-1928, and a music teacher and conductor at Vulcan’s Match Factory since 1918. He was also a city librarian in Tidaholm since 1930 and a conductor for both the Skövde Orchestra Association from 1915-1928 and the Falköping Orchestra Association from 1919-1926. He was the recipient of the Order of Vasa (RVO).
